# nginx/nginx.conf deliberately differs between main and staging (main
# reverse-proxies staging.*.com to the storybook-staging container; staging's
# own copy must NOT contain that block, or it proxies to itself in an
# infinite loop - see git history on the staging branch). `merge=binary` is
# a built-in git driver that forces a manual conflict whenever both sides
# have touched this file, instead of silently text-merging one branch's
# version over the other's.
nginx/nginx.conf merge=binary
